[SN]TITLE[SN]
Road in Brynmenyn, Bridgend, closed due to gas leak

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Engineers have closed a road in Bridgend county following concerns over a gas leak.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Temporary traffic lights will be put in place at the junction of Bryn Road and Abergarw Road in Brynmenyn after Wales and West Utilities was alerted to the smell of gas at about 9:50 GMT.
A spokesman said fixing the leak would be "a complex job" and did not yet know how long it could take.
No homes or businesses have been affected.
